node.text: Hi everyone, hope your all doing well! Its that time of the year again! Elections for next years e-board are underway and we want you to run!!! All of our current and previous members have said it’s a great experience and it has provided them with the unique opportunity of getting to know the team even better! If you are interested in running for a position use the link below or in our bio to see what positions are available and which might be right for you! Info about e-Board: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1q7Kht57rTVHNFTgH7LHhmXW_MsvaOLma_5vci7ZNheQ/edit?usp=sharing Registration form: https://forms.gle/EK4YeVCA93ZGaHL98

Hello everyone!! I’ve officially finished my degree credits at Rutgers so this will be my last post as RUCS Fundraising Chair. I joined Rutgers Club Swimming as a sophomore hoping to make friends and after missing the feeling of belonging to a team that I had felt competing in so many sports throughout my life. I am so thankful for this organization for allowing me to re-compete in the sport I love and form friendships that I otherwise wouldn’t have had at Rutgers. My favorite memories are definitely the van rides to away meets and hanging on the wall talking about politics for 50 minutes out of an hour of swimming. I will miss you all and I’m so excited to see what RUCS and future Exec Boards will bring in the future. Love, Maddie 🧜🏼‍♀️

That’s a wrap for summer 2020!! We’d like to conclude with an update from our Social Chair, Lilith 🥳
“I’ve been working at Seaside Heights where we set up fun events like drive-in movies and socially distant concerts! Like everyone else I have been watching too much TV and trying silly crafts. I miss you all greatly and can’t wait to see all of your beautiful faces at Werblin❤️”

We want to congratulate our Fundraising Chair, Maddie, on finishing her Capitol Hill internship this summer!! 🤩 Maddie says, “Over the last two and a half months, I served as a Legislative Intern for Congressman Van Drew. I attended various hearings on foreign affairs as well as natural resources, drafted press releases, and assisted in editing potential legislation.  I realize not everyone can say they’ve actively lived their dream, and I feel unbelievably fortunate to have done so.” Mad, we look forward to seeing you at Werblin and ~The White House~ soon!
